ronment of our world, ie not enemy teams, which are events covered under another section (though there are some similarities as noted below).<br>
<br>
First of all : All members of the Bringers of Retribution of at least rank 3 can post an event of this sort in the appropriate forum, containing the details needed for holding the event without too many problems happening underway. Rank 4 is required for hosting events concerning raids on enemy players, guilds, zones, etc. Rules for behaviours under such war raids are covered in another section of this book.<br>
<br>
The specific information required for posting an event should be as precise as possible, and include at least, but not limited to : time, place, goals, requirements of members, and how to get home. There will be a template for such events in the appropriate forum which you can copy for posting your event.<br>
<br>
At the current time all members who fullfill these requirements are allowed to post in that forum... but if control of it is lost because it is not used properly, we might take actions to restrict posting to certain chosen people.<br>
<br>
Some things to note about events and raids of this type: They do not need to concern attacking anything, obtaining any items or even moving at all. A tavern party in Kelethin is also an event in this category, as is a raid taking 12 people deep into Lower Guk to get a Short Sword of Ykesha.<br>
<br>
The main point of this is that events are ONLY posted on this board, and no other places will events be announced and regarded as guild held events. Gathering a group in game because there happen to be 6 people on who wants to go to Guk does not constitute an event such as this.<br>
<br>
Any events of this type also requires announcements in the forum at least 24 hours prior to the even, but we will be happy to see a large time period between announcing and hosting. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub86.ezboard.com/ukyrakasa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kyrakasa</A> at: 1/18/02 2:11:41 pm<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showPrevMessage?topicID=8.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showNextMessage?topicID=8.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.threadControl?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.tsa.nu/images/pix.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub86.ezboard.com/fbringersofretributionfrm16.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=8.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub86.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellsp